The evil that men do lives after them; the good is oft interred with their bones. So let it be with Caesar.
~ Shakespeare, &ldquo;Julius Caesar&rdquo;
Grok, if you can, the utter inability of human beings to describe other human beings neutrally. Almost all adjectives, even the most objective, become a value judgment when used to label a person&mdash;words like &ldquo;short&rdquo; and &ldquo;plump&rdquo; and &ldquo;withdrawn&rdquo; invoke an emotional response in many readers.
